1
02:22:52,844 --> 02:22:53,427
Watch out!

2
02:23:03,330 --> 02:23:05,148
What are you trying to do, drown us?

3
02:23:05,398 --> 02:23:07,984
I was born and bred on these waters,
Master Dwarf.

4
02:23:08,234 --> 02:23:09,610
If I wanted to drown you...

5
02:23:09,861 --> 02:23:11,446
...I would not do it here.

6
02:23:13,531 --> 02:23:15,950
Oh, I've had enough of this lippy Lakeman.

7
02:23:16,200 --> 02:23:18,953
I say we throw him over the side
and be done with him.

8
02:23:19,203 --> 02:23:21,664
- Bard, his name's Bard.
BOFUR: How do you know?

9
02:23:22,248 --> 02:23:23,666
Uh, I asked him.

10
02:23:23,916 --> 02:23:26,502
I don't care what he calls himself.
I don't like him.

11
02:23:26,752 --> 02:23:28,296
BALIN:
We do not have to like him.

12
02:23:28,546 --> 02:23:30,173
We simply have to pay him.

13
02:23:30,506 --> 02:23:33,426
Come on now, lads.
Turn out your pockets.

14
02:23:34,677 --> 02:23:36,262
How do we know he won't betray us?

15
02:23:36,512 --> 02:23:37,722
We don't.

16
02:23:38,681 --> 02:23:40,766
BALIN:
There's um... just a wee problem.

17
02:23:42,018 --> 02:23:43,436
We're 10 coins short.

18
02:23:45,605 --> 02:23:46,672
Gloin.

19
02:23:47,899 --> 02:23:50,860
- Come on. Give us what you have.
- Don't look to me.

20
02:23:51,944 --> 02:23:55,615
I have been bled dry by this venture.

21
02:23:55,948 --> 02:23:58,451
What have I seen for my investment?

22
02:23:59,285 --> 02:24:02,163
Naught but misery and grief and--

23
02:24:10,546 --> 02:24:12,506
GLOIN:
Bless my beard.

24
02:24:13,341 --> 02:24:14,509
Take it.

25
02:24:15,635 --> 02:24:17,011
- Take all of it.
- Ahem.

26
02:24:20,720 --> 02:24:22,048
The money, quick. Give it to me.

27
02:24:22,225 --> 02:24:24,894
THORIN: We will pay you when
we get our provisions but not before.

28
02:24:25,144 --> 02:24:27,605
If you value your freedom,
you'll do as I say.

29
02:24:28,064 --> 02:24:29,315
There are guards ahead.

30
02:24:42,380 --> 02:24:43,454
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

31
02:24:47,875 --> 02:24:49,252
What's he doing?

32
02:24:49,627 --> 02:24:50,795
BILBO:
He's talking to someone.

33
02:24:53,464 --> 02:24:54,549
He's pointing right at us.

34
02:24:57,927 --> 02:24:59,345
Now they're shaking hands.

35
02:24:59,595 --> 02:25:00,626
- What?

36
02:25:00,696 --> 02:25:02,599
DWALIN:
The villain. He's selling us out.

37
02:25:02,848 --> 02:25:03,808
[CLANKING]

38
02:25:04,100 --> 02:25:04,892
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

39
02:25:10,064 --> 02:25:11,899
[GRUNTING]

40
02:25:21,033 --> 02:25:23,202
[DWARVES GRUNTING]

41
02:25:25,621 --> 02:25:26,539
BARD:
Quiet.

42
02:25:29,333 --> 02:25:31,043
We're approaching the tollgate.

43
02:25:42,430 --> 02:25:43,264
PERCY:
Halt!

44
02:25:43,556 --> 02:25:44,890
Goods inspection!

45
02:25:45,641 --> 02:25:47,476
Papers, please!

46
02:25:48,269 --> 02:25:49,478
Oh, it's you, Bard.

47
02:25:49,729 --> 02:25:50,771
Morning, Percy.

48
02:25:51,022 --> 02:25:52,231
Anything to declare?

49
02:25:52,481 --> 02:25:55,234
Nothing, but that I am cold and tired...

50
02:25:55,484 --> 02:25:56,527
...and ready for home.

51
02:25:56,777 --> 02:25:58,029
You and me both.

52
02:26:02,116 --> 02:26:03,534
There we are.

53
02:26:03,784 --> 02:26:04,619
All in order.

